cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SI 

This paper deals with pedestrian trajectory prediction using social graph networks and stochastic methods. The most relevant sub-category is likely to be computer vision (cs.CV) as the paper deals with analyzing and predicting human motion. Machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) are also likely sub-categories as the paper proposes a network to collect social effects and accumulate with individual representation. Robotics (cs.RO) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with predicting human motion in crowded scenes, which is relevant to robotics applications. Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) is also a possible sub-category as the paper utilizes a directed social graph to model social behaviors.
